article.description: Zay Williams had 16 points as Troy beat Jacksonville State 60-55 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Williams carries Troy past Jacksonville St. 60-55
article.linkText: Williams carries Troy past Jacksonville St. 60-55
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Zay Williams had 16 points as Troy beat Jacksonville State 60-55 on Wednesday night. Darian Adams had 14 points for Troy (4-6), which held the Gamecocks to five points over the final 9:25 in ending its four-game road losing streak. Kayne Henry had 14 points and eight rebounds for the Gamecocks (2-7), who have now lost four games in a row. De'Torrion Ware added 13 points and six rebounds and Elias Harden had 12 points. Troy plays Chattanooga on the road on Sunday. Jacksonville State plays Evansville at home on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
